comments: This study was all about pattern recognition. I quickly noticed that each symbol started with a certain prefix. For example, asterisk = gafi, star = zeti, pentagon = buvi, donut circle = wopi. Then, each color also represented a certain suffix. For example, yellow = she and sometimes se, dark blue = se, lighter blue = fu, red = ho. Then, based on the image and color I was shown, I would combine the corresponding prefix and suffix. For example, a red donut circle = wopiho. Initially, I took notes when I first noticed the patterns. So, I would write down "star = zeti" and "red = ho" for example. But I very quickly didn't need to refer to this list. I could easily remember the patterns. The most confusing aspect was that yellow was sometimes "she" and sometimes "se." So, that was initially difficult to keep track of. I didn't rely on the pronunciations very much because some suffixes sounded very similar. It helped a lot to be able to read the word.
